data.title: Libhtscodecs-dev
data.description: Custom compression for CRAM and others.
data.name: htscodecs

evidence: "This repository implements the custom CRAM codecs used for \"EXTERNAL\" block types." (library-style codecs intended to be used by other software)

"The library can be used as a git sub-module or as a completely separate entity.  If you are attempting to make use of these codecs within your own library, such as we do within Staden io_lib" (used as a dependency library)

Build and usage instructions are via cloning and building from source: "If building from git, you'll need to recreate the configure script... From then on, it follows the normal \"./configure; make\"" (no mention of package registries or binaries)
